    "details": {
      "blurb": "Scarlet walker of Leng — Sorshen's bound guardian (B15)",
      "languages": {
        "details": "",
        "value": [
          "aklo",
          "infernal",
          "thassilonian"
        ]
      },
      "level": {
        "value": 17
      },
      "privateNotes": "",
      "publicNotes": "<p><strong>Role (B15):</strong> a <strong>scarlet walker</strong> — last of the spindle-legged horrors Sorshen drew from the nightmare realm of <strong>Leng</strong> eleven thousand years ago as advisors on the Everdawn Pool, bound to the Sunken Queen as an immortal guardian. It resented Ileosa until she proved her skill with the Pool and <strong>promised to release it home to Leng</strong> when her ritual ends. It holds the Great Hall (B15), and climbs to the Pool (B20) to join the final battle if it still lives.</p>",
      "publication": {
        "title": "Pathfinder: Curse of the Crimson Throne (PF2e conversion, private)",
